22using LevelEstimatorType =
23 AudioProcessing::Config::GainController2::LevelEstimator;
24
25float ClampLevelEstimateDbfs(float level_estimate_dbfs) {
26 return rtc::SafeClamp<float>(level_estimate_dbfs, -90.f, 30.f);
27}

29} // namespace

31bool AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::LevelEstimatorState::operator==(
32 const AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::LevelEstimatorState& b) const {
33 return time_to_confidence_ms == b.time_to_confidence_ms &&
34 level_dbfs.numerator == b.level_dbfs.numerator &&
35 level_dbfs.denominator == b.level_dbfs.denominator;
36}
37
38float AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::LevelEstimatorState::Ratio::GetRatio() const {
39 RTC_DCHECK_NE(denominator, 0.f);
40 return numerator / denominator;
41}
42
43AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator(
44 ApmDataDumper* apm_data_dumper)
45 : AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator(
46 apm_data_dumper,
47 kDefaultLevelEstimatorAdjacentSpeechFramesThreshold) {}
48
49AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator(
50 ApmDataDumper* apm_data_dumper,
51 int adjacent_speech_frames_threshold)
52 : apm_data_dumper_(apm_data_dumper),
53 adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_(adjacent_speech_frames_threshold),
54 level_dbfs_(ClampLevelEstimateDbfs(kInitialSpeechLevelEstimateDbfs)) {
55 RTC_DCHECK(apm_data_dumper_);
56 RTC_DCHECK_GE(adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_, 1);
57 Reset();
58}
59
60void AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::Update(
61 const VadLevelAnalyzer::Result& vad_level) {
62 RTC_DCHECK_GT(vad_level.rms_dbfs, -150.f);
63 RTC_DCHECK_LT(vad_level.rms_dbfs, 50.f);
64 RTC_DCHECK_GT(vad_level.peak_dbfs, -150.f);
65 RTC_DCHECK_LT(vad_level.peak_dbfs, 50.f);
66 RTC_DCHECK_GE(vad_level.speech_probability, 0.f);
67 RTC_DCHECK_LE(vad_level.speech_probability, 1.f);
68 if (vad_level.speech_probability < kVadConfidenceThreshold) {
69 // Not a speech frame.
70 if (adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_ > 1) {
71 // When two or more adjacent speech frames are required in order to update
72 // the state, we need to decide whether to discard or confirm the updates
73 // based on the speech sequence length.
74 if (num_adjacent_speech_frames_ >= adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_) {
75 // First non-speech frame after a long enough sequence of speech frames.
76 // Update the reliable state.
77 reliable_state_ = preliminary_state_;
78 } else if (num_adjacent_speech_frames_ > 0) {
79 // First non-speech frame after a too short sequence of speech frames.
80 // Reset to the last reliable state.
81 preliminary_state_ = reliable_state_;
82 }
83 }
84 num_adjacent_speech_frames_ = 0;
85 } else {
86 // Speech frame observed.
87 num_adjacent_speech_frames_++;
88
89 // Update preliminary level estimate.
90 RTC_DCHECK_GE(preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms, 0);
91 const bool buffer_is_full = preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms == 0;
92 if (!buffer_is_full) {
93 preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms -= kFrameDurationMs;
94 }
95 // Weighted average of levels with speech probability as weight.
96 RTC_DCHECK_GT(vad_level.speech_probability, 0.f);
97 const float leak_factor = buffer_is_full ? kLevelEstimatorLeakFactor : 1.f;
98 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.numerator =
99 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.numerator * leak_factor +
100 vad_level.rms_dbfs * vad_level.speech_probability;
101 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.denominator =
102 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.denominator * leak_factor +
103 vad_level.speech_probability;
104
105 const float level_dbfs = preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.GetRatio();
106
107 if (num_adjacent_speech_frames_ >= adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_) {
108 // `preliminary_state_` is now reliable. Update the last level estimation.
109 level_dbfs_ = ClampLevelEstimateDbfs(level_dbfs);
110 }
111 }
112 DumpDebugData();
113}
114
115bool AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::IsConfident() const {
116 if (adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_ == 1) {
117 // Ignore `reliable_state_` when a single frame is enough to update the
118 // level estimate (because it is not used).
119 return preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms == 0;
120 }
121 // Once confident, it remains confident.
122 RTC_DCHECK(reliable_state_.time_to_confidence_ms != 0 ||
123 preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms == 0);
124 // During the first long enough speech sequence, `reliable_state_` must be
125 // ignored since `preliminary_state_` is used.
126 return reliable_state_.time_to_confidence_ms == 0 ||
127 (num_adjacent_speech_frames_ >= adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_ &&
128 preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms == 0);
129}
130
131void AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::Reset() {
132 ResetLevelEstimatorState(preliminary_state_);
133 ResetLevelEstimatorState(reliable_state_);
134 level_dbfs_ = ClampLevelEstimateDbfs(kInitialSpeechLevelEstimateDbfs);
135 num_adjacent_speech_frames_ = 0;
136}
137
138void AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::ResetLevelEstimatorState(
139 LevelEstimatorState& state) const {
140 state.time_to_confidence_ms = kLevelEstimatorTimeToConfidenceMs;
141 state.level_dbfs.numerator = kInitialSpeechLevelEstimateDbfs;
142 state.level_dbfs.denominator = 1.0f;
143}
144
145void AdaptiveModeLevelEstimator::DumpDebugData() const {
146 apm_data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
147 "agc2_adaptive_level_estimator_num_adjacent_speech_frames",
148 num_adjacent_speech_frames_);
149 apm_data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
150 "agc2_adaptive_level_estimator_preliminary_level_estimate_num",
151 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.numerator);
152 apm_data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
153 "agc2_adaptive_level_estimator_preliminary_level_estimate_den",
154 preliminary_state_.level_dbfs.denominator);
155 apm_data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
156 "agc2_adaptive_level_estimator_preliminary_time_to_confidence_ms",
157 preliminary_state_.time_to_confidence_ms);
158 apm_data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
159 "agc2_adaptive_level_estimator_reliable_time_to_confidence_ms",
160 reliable_state_.time_to_confidence_ms);
161}
